Package org.neo4j.kernel.impl.util.collection

Class HeapTrackingOrderedAppendMap<K,​V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.internal.kernel.api.DefaultCloseListenable
      • org.neo4j.kernel.impl.util.collection.HeapTrackingOrderedAppendMap<K,​V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - key type
    V - value type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, AutoCloseablePlus
    public class HeapTrackingOrderedAppendMap<K,​V>
extends DefaultCloseListenable
    A heap tracking, ordered, append-only, map. It only tracks the internal structure, not the elements within. Elements are also inserted in a single-linked list to allow traversal from first to last in the order of insertion. No replacement of existing elements is possible.

(This is to avoid having to unnecessarily implement a slow linear scan through the singly-linked list to find and replace the entry)

      • autoClosingEntryIterator

        public Iterator<Map.Entry<K,​V>> autoClosingEntryIterator()
        After calling this you can only consume the existing entries through the returned iterator. The map will be closed and no further entries can be added. When the iterator is exhausted it will call close() automatically. (Everything allocated by the function given to getIfAbsentPutWithMemoryTracker() will then also be released when the scoped memory tracker is closed.) WARNING: The entries returned by next() are transient and must be consumed before calling next() again!
